Check out this awesome deck in action here: https://youtu.be/rwmLnW8dSjM

Fill free to subscribe and like the video if you'd enjoy'd it &#x1f60e;

Any doubts or questions let me know &#x1f642;

I almost never summon gren with this deck because its easier to use gizmek, hex trude or the danger cards to summon Aegion or Dragulion and Armillyre.

Make sure to abuse soul absorption and save a necroface just in case.

&nbsp;

Hey guys, Mi-ka-yo here, using another account to upload an entire GAMBLING DECK!  This is not like the Swordsman of Landstar deck, that deck had a lot more cards that didn't revolve around gambling.  With this one, I found the best and worst gambling cards that I could, put them together, and shared them for others to enjoy.

&nbsp;

I started with a deck called "Gamble Mania" that I downloaded a long time ago by somebody that I wouldn't be able to tell you the name of right now.  I completely gutted most of it, gave it much more cards, and an extra deck that really is nothing to write home about.........

&nbsp;

I believe that the point of this deck is to keep your opponents guessing so that you can have the upper hand (if the cards you have don't screw you over).  The gamble is the name of the game and I hope that you like it!

&nbsp;

Enjoy,

Mi-ka-yo

Use spells and traps and monsters to kill weak opponet. You can troll them hard.

